  Source: tsb_interpreter.txt  (interpreter lines 73338–79071)
  Reference: LastBreathNew_Apply_2.lua  (canonical helper source)
================================================================================

  EXTRACTION SUMMARY
  ------------------
  This file was built using the same process documented in LastBreathNew_Apply_2.lua.
  The Terrible Tornado block (5,734 lines in the interpreter) was extracted
  verbatim from the v12 if/elseif chain, the opening "elseif" was changed to
  "if" since it is now the first branch, and all helpers were pulled from the
  LastBreathNew_Apply_2.lua reference file rather than re-derived from the
  interpreter (to preserve fixes already applied there).

  PAYLOAD FIELDS  (v1090 for Terrible Tornado)
  ---------------------------------------------
  v1090.root   → HumanoidRootPart of the attacker's character (BasePart)
  v1090.hit    → The TARGET character model (Model) — used for:
                   • Face/hair accessory transparency resets
                   • Sound parenting to hit.Head / hit.Torso
                   • PointLight positioning over hit.Torso
                   • Ground Crater placement at hit position
  v1090.id     → Numeric animation ID (no "rbxassetid://" prefix).
                 The block finds the playing animation track by matching:
                   v15388.Animation.AnimationId == "rbxassetid://" .. l_id_34
                 If no matching track is found, v15370 = nil and ALL
                 marker-driven VFX (velstart, velend, punch, cutscene) are
                 silently skipped. The animation MUST be loaded and playing
                 before v12 is called.
  v1090.Seed   → Number; seeds crater randomisation for cross-client
                 determinism. Pass math.random() or a fixed value.

  NEW DEPENDENCY vs LastBreathNew_Apply_2.lua
  -------------------------------------------
  v780 / shared.loop
      Fixed-rate loop runner. Used by the floating debris loop inside the
      [420] frame handler at interpreter line 74224. Not present in the LBN
      file — added here directly below the v717 block.

  l_Cutscenes_0
      game.ReplicatedStorage.Cutscenes folder. Used by the "cutscene" animation
      marker handler at interpreter line 77841:
        require(l_Cutscenes_0["Terrible Tornado"])
      Declared in the globals section of this file.

  TERRIBLETORNADO  (bare global)
      Module cache. The block does:
        local v16194 = TERRIBLETORNADO or require(l_Cutscenes_0["Terrible Tornado"])
        if not TERRIBLETORNADO then TERRIBLETORNADO = v16194 end
      Initialized as nil here; populated on first cutscene-marker fire.

  BUGS FIXED (same as LBN file)
  ------------------------------
  v294 = tick()        — v301 cleanup timer. Missing from all extracted files.
                         Added to globals. Without it v301 crashes on every
                         v471 call with "arithmetic on nil".
  v472 = { workspace.Live, workspace.Thrown }
                       — Default RaycastParams filter for v717. Added to
                         globals. Without it raycasts hit everything.

  ANIMATION-DRIVEN ARCHITECTURE
  ------------------------------
  Unlike Last Breath New (which fires immediately), Terrible Tornado is 100%
  marker-driven. All VFX are connected to animation marker signals:
    "velstart"  → attaches BodyVelocity and begins speed tween to 125
    "velend"    → tweens speed back to 1
    "punch"     → plays punch impact sound on hit.Head
    "cutscene"  → loads the Terrible Tornado cutscene module and starts
                  the full RenderStepped camera/VFX sequence (shockwaves,
                  rocks, lighting, DragWind, etc.)
  The Stopped signal on the track cleans up all Maid connections.
  If the animation finishes or is stopped early, cleanup fires automatically.

  EFFECTS CALLED INTERNALLY (not present in this file)
  -----------------------------------------------------
  "Backhand"   — called at interpreter line 74274 inside the [420] frame
                 handler when v15375 (local-player gate) is true.
                 Falls silently through the v12 chain here.

  ENTRY POINT
  -----------
  The entry point at the bottom of this file:
    1. Gets the local player's character and HumanoidRootPart
    2. Creates and plays the Terrible Tornado animation
    3. Passes root, hit, id, Seed to v12

  REPLACE THE ANIMATION ID:
    TORNADO_ANIM_ID below must be set to the real Terrible Tornado animation
    asset ID (numeric, no "rbxassetid://" prefix). The effect will not fire
    any VFX until a track matching that ID is found in GetPlayingAnimationTracks.

